Ever wondered how to write code inside Excel? 🚀 In this step-by-step beginner tutorial, I’ll show you how to get started with VBA (Visual Basic for Applications) — Excel’s built-in programming language. You’ll learn how to create your first macro, write useful VBA code, and even attach it to a button to automate tasks instantly.

Whether you’re completely new to coding or just curious about what Excel can really do, this tutorial will help you unlock the power of automation and take your spreadsheets to the next level.

👉 What you’ll learn in this video:

How to enable the Developer tab

How to record your first macro

Writing VBA code in the editor

Creating a “Hello World” program

Building a useful VBA macro (highlight duplicates)

Adding a button to run your code

Best practices for saving and organizing your VBA projects
